,Recommended,251170,7315025,"Posted: 5 October, 2013",all,AzoNe,"REVIEW OUTDATED!-----------------------------------------------------------------------------This game.. What can i say? Its Alpha 0.42 so theres not much to say really.But what i can say, is that this game is awesome! So heres my opinion/look on it.What is Damned?: Its a co-op/multiplayer horror game where you can play as either the survivor that has to get all the keys and escape, or the monster that sets up traps to scare the hell out of everybody and causing panic and has the job of ""getting rid of the survivors"".Map designs: I do like how the maps are designed, but sometimes its very hard to find the keys, but i like that it spawns randomly. I like the maps though.Graphics, music and sound effects: The graphics arent bad, but neither very good either, its decent. But at the moment theres a need for optimization to fix the FPS issues that are there. It is Alpha after all. It runs just fine on my pc though, but it still seems kind of laggy, even with 60 FPS.I really like the music and sound effects in this game, creepy, unexpected and makes it all much more scary, which is good. This has a connection with the traps that the monster can set up, i like it.I just think that the monster has a lack of sound effects, he has none actually. So, i think it would be great with some creepy ones added to the monster(s).Playstyles:Playing as the ""Survivor"": I will say that i dont dislike playing as the survivor, cause it can actually be quite fun, for me at least. Gathering keys, sticking together with your teammates, escaping the monster when hes chasing you and stuff, its all quite fun. You have a flashlight which you can turn on and off, its very useful if the monster is chasing you, you can just turn it off and youre pretty much invisible.Playing as the ""Monster"": This is a playstyle ive never seen before, to be honest, which is cool. It was quite confusing to me in the start what to actually do, but i figured it out quite fast. If you know where you have your survivors, its just hilarious to play as the monster. There is 2 forms that you can go in to;1. The physical form, this is where you can see the survivors, kill them, and they can see you. You walk very slow but can one-hit kill people and still set traps.2. The ghost form, this is where you are invisible, can walk through doors and set up traps around the map.Its quite fun, because you can just spawn right in front of them and scare them and see them run away.Conclusion: I like this game, its unique and very fun (and scary).If i should rate it, i think i would rate it 5 or 6/10, just because its very good, but it can also get boring very quickly. What i think it needs, is just updates, which is coming. New monsters, maps and objectives. Theres a new monster thats in work in progress right now actually, im excited for that.End thoughts:So, to end it off, gather 4 friends if you can and play it together, thats the most fun.Also a good LAN Party game. It doesnt cost much and its a lot of fun. The developers seem to work quite good on this game, so im looking forward to the future updates!6/10"
76561197966610945,Not Recommended,251170,12685190,"Posted: 29 October, 2014",all,Geriatrix,"I should start by saying that the game did provide a few sessions of fun. That being said, there are a number of problems with the game:1. The premise is very narrow and wears thin quickly. At first it is scary and you die all the time. Then you realise that you cannot possibly complete this game (see point 2) without studying the particulars of the monster you are facing. The minute you do that, the scary aspect pretty much disappears, or in the very least much of it is lost.2. The game is extremely hard for the survivors. The only way to beat it is to treat it like any other computer game and learn specific strategies... but in a game so dependent on atmosphere and fright, this ruins things.3. Once you have your strategy in place, studied the monster to the point where there is nothing scary about it, and are ready to play, you will soon find the game becoming very repetitive and tedious. You will essentially wander around in the dark trying to find that one damn key that no one could find to the door that is still locked. After 20 minutes of going around in the same circle doing nothing but trying to imagine where on earth you forgot to look and you will be ready to pull your hair clean off your head.4. The door opening and closing mechanism is moronic. You will not believe how moronic it is if you did not try it.All in all, not a game I would recommend. Interesting idea, but not very well executed and also lacking in content to make it interesting in the long run."
,Recommended,251170,20305931,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,Toxic League,"Damned is a 4 vs 1 cooperative game where 4 survivors are trapped inside a location such as an asylum, hospital, or hotel trying to escape the horror that lies within. In order to escape, keys must be located and boards must be removed to open the final exit door all while avoiding a deadly monster. There are 4 different types of monsters that a group can play against. Each monster has its own unique abilities to locate and kill the survivors and each survivor has a different set of attributes. This leads to a lot of cat and mouse tactics in knowing where to look and when to run and hide.There's about 10 different maps, a few different game modes, and key placement is randomized each game.The game has a small learning curve which involves each monster's playing strategy to efficiently locate and kill the survivors, and as a survivor understanding where keys typically are hidden and learning to avoid and escape each monster. It is a very satisfying game after learning the fundamentals, but until that point I felt kind of lost.There are typically a handful of games going although it is often difficult to find a public game because the game has a very small player base and the majority of games available are private. You may also have to wait several minutes for a spot to open up or people to join your game, but if you already have a small group of friends that won't be a problem."
