,Recommended,251170,8389121,"Posted: 28 December, 2013",all,Cipherpunk,"Is it buggy? Hell yeah, this is an alpha afterall.Is it fun? Dear God, yes.This is one of the most tense and dynamic experiences I've had playing a game with friends in forever. There's is something so heart-poundingly terrifying about being hunted by a living, breathing monster that cannot be fooled with AI pathing tricks. It WILL find you because it thinks just like you; therefore you cannot, MUST NOT, think like you. Pure genius.It took a couple games/crashes and some trial and error to find what works and what doesn't. But half a dozen games in, our schoolgirl giggling chatter evolved into concise, razor sharp planning. It has layers of depth to it as you get better, both for the survivors and the monster. I cannot recommend Damned more highly."
