,Recommended,251170,26411274,"Posted: 3 November, 2016",all,SerenityVerdant,"Okay! So this game is fantastic. I know people compare this to Dead by Daylight, but I actually think this game is better. Are the graphics better? No. I like the scavanging aspect of it along with actually feeling haunted, not being chased down by a crazy murderer, but that's my own bias towards the paranormal...The controls do take getting used to and the controller support is♥♥♥♥♥♥ However, the atmosphere is great for people who love horror games and jump scares. The monsters are well balanced. Though sometimes Mary can be a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥because of how fast she is, side stepping and running around obstacles (like chairs, tables, and closing doors) are your best ways of dealing with her. It does take some time, effort, and a bit of memory to remember what you have and have not checked in order to get out. Doors are difficult to open at times, but every person I've played with seems to gain their own little strategy for it. Batteries and keys are SMALL, so you much pay attention to the tiny glowing things. Remember where you have seen batteries for the times you can't pick them up. On some maps, you have to return to the beginning to get something that was locked in a safe so you can move on.Because there is no tutorial, this is a game you have to take the time to study. I had a friend be a monster while not attacking me in order to get used to things. This game is also much, much, much more fun with multiple friends. I recommend at least 1 monster and 2-3 survivors. If you can get all four, great!Things we figured out through playing that others might need some help on...1) You can open some drawers and cabinets. (I know there are pictures of an open stuff in the example images on the store page, but my friends and I assumed that they were already open. We were wrong.)2) HOLD AND DRAG/PUSH TO OPEN DOORS. It's not a ""push d and door opens"" thing. You have to manually open them.3) When playing Mary: She is slow as hell, so be prepared for that. She randomly teleports if you don't kill the survivors on time. You can sometimes get lucky and teleport right behind the survivors. Your ""energy"" is based on how much color you have on your screen; the more color, the more energy. You can manually teleport as well.4) The Lurker and the Fallen are trap based monsters. I don't entirely understand them yet, so I can't say much here.5) The Phantom is pretty straight forward. Survivors are invisible to it, but the survivors can see him. Stealth is key for the survivors here. Music starts when you've sensed them. Look around and chase them down. If you stand inside a survivor that's hiding, you auto-detect them.My friends and I checked the Wiki to figure some of this out, but most was trial and error. Highly recommend this game."
