,Not Recommended,251170,16103900,"Posted: 31 May, 2015",all,King Gibbon,"I have recommended this game numerous times to many friends and have enjoyed many games of this. But why do I not recommend this to game to the general public? Well when I started playing, it was classed as early access. Pretty decent for early access. Very fun and was quite low on the game breaking bug spectrum. Sure there were a few crashes here and there, was poorly optimised and desyncs but it was early access. But now, the game is classed as a full release and bugs that should have been ironed out have been left it seems. Not to mention a new bug having risen its head.Keys that open doors are being swapped with keys to rooms you cannot get to before you unlock the doors before them. So you have a key that will open a kitchen, but to get to the kitchen you have to open the dining hall or pantry. But the keys have not spawned in an accessible area. This has happened a few times now  since release. We never used to have this issue but it seems to be a regular occurrence for us now. We are still getting disconnects and regular desyncs where players will see their team mates walking into walls. The once extremely regular patches have slowed down a lot and the amount of players which was never very high, has dropped hugely. Not that it matters for me as I have friends who I play with which, if you buy this is a necessity. This game is pretty crap to play with random people. Get a call going with friends and just play with them. If you don't have friends, there is such a little player base now that you will probably not find a match.TL:;DR This game should not have left early access at all as most of the alpha bugs are still present. Sure its a fun game with friends, but the bugs just ruin it completely."
