,Not Recommended,251170,13708306,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,BEEP BEEP BOOP,"Damned has the potential to be a good game, but it isn't. Atleast in it's current state. The game still has some annoying bugs. Whenever someone hosts a game, they choose when to start the game. If the host starts the game before everyone has loaded in, the game crashes for whoever has not loaded in yet and their character instantly dies. It took us a little while to figure out why this was happening, but once we figured it out the bug was easy to avoid. Also, I noticed the game tends to crash if you choose to play multiple rounds within the same lobby. Aside from all the bugs, the gameplay isn't anything to write home about. The monsters/ghosts kill the survivors really easily, but the monsters can choose to drag the match out and attempt to scare the survivors before slaughtering them. In most of the public matches I've played, the monsters just straight up kill you within the first few minutes of the match. They don't attempt to scare you whatsoever, which makes for some lackluster gameplay. If you somehow make it past the ten minute mark, your character starts to have a psychotic break. The longer you go without beating the game(escaping), or getting killed, the symptoms intensify. For instance, hands start to come out the floor which prevent the player from moving. I won't spoil anymore of the symptoms for those who choose to buy the game. One weird thing about the whole psychotic break thing is that all the symptoms are completely clientside, meaning your teammates can't see any of the symptoms you are currently experiencing. I guess this is because it's all in your head, right?If you choose to buy this game, I suggest you play it with a group of friends. If you don't have a group of friends to play with, then don't bother with this game."
