76561197987357391,Recommended,251170,7759018,"Posted: 25 November, 2013",all,Kleid,"Ho man, do I love this game.  At the time of writing this review, the game is still in alpha.  That being said, for a game at this stage of development, it's a solid game.  The concept is original and the execution is already good and still morphing into something even better as the developers receive feedback.  It's fund being both the humans and the monster, though between the two currently available (lurker and phantom) the lurker is definitely the favoured one.  The challenge exists for both the humans and the monster since the humans always have that feeling of dread that the monster is around every corner and struggling to advance while the monster is actually on the other side of the map desparately trying to claw his way out of a closet trying to find the last survivor.  I would say it's a definite winner with a good amount of replayability either with friends or online with strangers,"
,Recommended,251170,7762085,"Posted: 26 November, 2013",all,Nick,"This CO-OP survival game is shaping up to become something that I've been longing for on any platform. Up to four players trying to survive certain doom in different maps and searching for keys with only a flashlight in hand can be really intense. Especially when you know the enemy (a player-controlled monster that can go from invisible to visible in the blink of an eye) is lurking around every corner. Might even be walking right behind without you knowing it.This is a game that needs the players to cooperate to survive. As a monster your sole purpose is to make sure the humans won't get away. Afterall they're yours to feast upon.The game is still in alpha and needs more work and polish. There are not many maps or monsters but they're coming. The developers are hard at work and I've seen this game change since I first bought it. Even though it's still in alpha this game delivers plenty of fun, especially for LAN with friends. While playing with random people can be fun this game really delivers when playing with people you know. This is where Damned really shines!If you, like me, is longing for a cooperative, atmospheric horror title which is not centered around shooting things this might be for you! If your tired of being able to kill everything in your path, no matter how great the danger, and want something that can keep you on the edge of your seat, delivering a different experience every time this is for you. If you enjoy being able to rip every other player apart this is also for you!I'm really enjoying this game and I'm looking forward to see it evolve into a finished product."
