76561198060784066,Recommended,251170,26965929,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,Dennis the Menace,"I played this game in a pre-Dead by Daylightworld and it was great fun. Keeping in mind that it's only really enjoyable if you play it with friends,Damnedis a charming little title that provided us with a few good hours of enjoyment. Whilst it can be compared toDepth, Dead by Daylightand the upcomingLast Year, this game has a certain pizzazz that those other games do not. The act of scavenging for your escape, rather than fixing or waiting for a generator makes ones actions seem all the more desperate as the player spends each second actively participating in their own escape attempt. This being said, the games has many flaws, yet some of these flaws actually contribute to the overall appeal of the game. Some flaws include those of how back when I played (this may have changed in recent times) there was really only one monster worth playing. The servers also had some issues yet with a bit of patience we were always able to play. Also, when you died and went into spectator mode it seemed as though watching your allies in first person perspective mode was even more fluid and had more animations than when you yourself were playing (and this is one of the flaws that gave the game its charm).This is a flawed game. But it's a fun game (with friends). Although there are now some better alternatives as aforementioned,Damnedstill has its own thrills and surprises. I would not buy this game at full price, instead wait for the many sales and buy it then, perhaps even a four-pack to play with your friends."
